<br>
At 46, or even at 56, you needn't worry too much about obtaining it for it's status. Often the difficulty in obtaining the Green Scale prevents completion. This is more indicative of the size of your guild and luck than ability as a Warrior.<br>
<br>
A mid-level Warrior weilding a Sebilite Croaking Dirk (or better yet a Willsapper) and a Frostbringer is adequately armed IMO.<br>
<br>
Yes, I was thrilled when I obtained my Epic at level 60. Two months later I was weilding a Twisted Steel Bastard Sword 53/45 25AC 10STR 10STA 7 save all and am contemplating leaving the Epic in the bank. If I manage to get a Willsapper or better, I might use the Blade of Strategy when MTing, but I'll be very aware that the Epic needs to be replaced.<br>
<br>
The Warrior Epic causes lower level players to &quot;Oooh and Ahhh&quot;, but by the time you get it, you often don't need it. Hang on to the Fungi.<br>
<br>
